DDL: Data Definition Language
  It is used to define database structure or schema.

  The various statements under the DDL are:
   a) CREATE: It is used to create new objects in a database
   b) ALTER: It is used to alter the structure of a database
   c) DROP: It is used to delete the structure of a table in a database
   d) TRUNCATE: It is use to remove all the records from a table
   e) COMMENT: It is used to add comment
   f) RENAME: It is used to rename an object

